            "Cape Canaveral not.But here, coast, spit land past Border Patrol checkpoint, Rio Grande meets Gulf Mexico, spaceship assembled State Highway 4 dead-ends sea.Towering stainless-steel shiny, looks like surreal sculpture amid cactuses, yucca relentless South Texas sun. And, it’s built factory open, it’s roadside attraction, drawing gawkers area remote county trucks drinking water month live nearby.They’re coming Elon Musk’s latest creation, prototype called Starship hopes day carry people dozens moon Mars. Musk, presentation Saturday, said goal building “rapidly reusable spacecraft” lead fulfillment ultimate goal creating “a city Mars.” first, he’ll need pull improbable feat, building private, commercial spaceport here, local elected official called “mind-boggling” juxtaposition: SpaceX, hottest companies world, led Silicon Valley celebrity nearly 29 million Twitter followers, building rocket border town nearly residents live poverty line.“I million years imagined it,” said Cameron County Judge Eddie Treviño Jr. years ago, SpaceX started building launchpad here, hauling dirt ton, allow company measure freedom restraints come shooting rockets government sites, Cape Canaveral Vandenberg Air Force Base California, companies operate. “This going new kind spaceport optimized commercial operations,” Musk said groundbreaking ceremony 2014. “Cape Canaveral Cape Vandenberg great launch sites, military launch sites.”The company welcomed local officials Walt Disney-like messiah help spark economic revival area desperately needs it. state set aside $15.3 million help company build facilities bought SpaceX’s vision transform area commercial spaceport sending people solar system.“You know term ‘visionary’; they’re ones world 'round,” Treviño said. Outside county courthouse, downtown replete boarded-up businesses. Real estate prices depressed. Schools surrounded security fences. years, area caught unending “vicious cycle,” Treviño said, bad people “are fortunate college 