ys saw dozen them. Sixty-three corpses found all, according local turtle-protection group. deaths determined related illegal fishing, incident threw sharp relief fragile world SpaceX expanding empire. READ SPACEX, realized radical vision future actually was—not hypothetical journeys Mars near-term ambitions. company seeking approval launch thousand satellites Starlink program, Google- Fidelity-funded endeavor bring high-speed Internet rural areas expedite international financial transactions. Starlink allow SpaceX capture portion trillion-dollar global telecommunications industry. goes according plan, times SpaceX-launched satellites sky visible stars. Starship—and Boca Chica—is key making reality. Falcon 9 rocket hold dozen satellites, Starship hundred. Musk said he’d like launches day Boca Chica. “I calculation—that’s billion pounds fuel year,” said Dave Mosher, reporter Business Insider covers SpaceX. “I don’t think fuel fast enough.” correcting Musk’s characteristic overstatements, likely Boca Chica soon poor people’s beach community fixed-income retirees busy industrial corridor. Indeed, beginnings liquefied-natural-gas export facility Port Brownsville visible horizon. returned Boca Chica late December, imagined I’d find depressed, depleted place. Instead, tumultuous year, community infused fresh spirit. Residents come terms SpaceX’s presence, better worse. rocket intrusive, neighbor, unlike them, stay. some, incentive hash agreement company. “I jumped ship sank,” Cheryl told me. sitting living room, thrift-shop decor she’d carefully amassed years here. “I’m going find cheap home else, probably different state, I’m disgusted Texas. I’m going try re-create life.” SpaceX granted March out, determined final winter beach. resolved fight. press time, dozen homeowners refused sell. thought better offer SpaceX waited—a risky gamble, company said three-times offer table. wanted time. holdouts included rocket’s biggest fans Boca Chica. now, Mary micro-influencer rabid c